item.title: 57% of Roads Sub Standard, Agency Says
item.description: More than half of Russia's federal highway system — 27,619 kilometers of roads — is not up to standards, according to the Federal Highways Agency. "In the 1960s we built roads to meet different burdens. Only a third of federal roads today can support a vehicle carrying more than 10 tons per axle," Igor Astakhov, head of the department for road operation at the Federal Highways Agency, said at a conference in Tomsk on Wednesday, Interfax reported. Twenty-seven percent — 13,015 kilometers — of Russia's roads are overloaded, he said.

item.title: Montell Jordan Shares Story On Journey From R&B Singer To A Pastor
item.description: Former R&B singer Montell Jordan still remains a staple artist on everyone’s kickback playlist, even though he’s found a new passion in the church. The Cali native rose to stardom in the early 90s with his infectious hit “This Is How We Do It,” that sat atop the charts in 1995. Making history as Def Jam’s first R&B release, the melody was later followed up by his collaborations with No Limit’s Master P and Silkk the Shocker, and garnered songwriting credits for a countless number of R&B jams, including Deborah Cox’s vocally-challenging “Nobody’s Supposed to Be Here.

item.title: Study Says Blood Test Can Tell Fetal Sex At 7 Weeks
item.description: This is interesting, and probably good news for expectant parents. Via NY Times: A simple blood test that can determine a baby’s sex as early as seven weeks into pregnancy is highly accurate if used correctly, a finding that experts say is likely to lead to more widespread use by parents concerned about gender-linked diseases, those who are merely curious and people considering the more ethically controversial step of selecting the sex of their children.

item.description: ATLANTIC BEACH, N.C., Sept. 1, 2021 /PRNewswire/ -- Today, the Insurance Institute for Business & Home Safety (IBHS) celebrated its 30,000th FORTIFIED Home™ designation at a home in Atlantic Beach, NC. The home's resilient roof was funded in part by the Strengthen Your Roof program operated by the North Carolina Insurance Underwriting Association (NCIUA) and meets the stringent resilience requirements of the FORTIFIED program.  Based on research by IBHS, FORTIFIED is a voluntary set of above-code design, building, and retrofitting steps that strengthen homes against severe weather.

item.title: Ariana Grande Includes Late Mac Miller on 'Yours Truly' Rerelease
item.description: Ariana Grande included a special nod to late ex Mac Miller while putting a new spin on her debut album, Yours Truly. Grande, 30, dropped a new deluxe version of her 2013 record on Friday, August 25, to celebrate its milestone anniversary. Along with the tracks fans know and love, the expanded edition of Yours Truly featured two fresh takes on her duet with Miller titled “The Way” — a “Live From London” version and a “Spanglish” version.

item.title: Jennifer Lawrence: "My Breasts Are Uneven!"
item.description: Jennifer Lawrence made an alleged confession on Jimmy Kimmel Live Thursday, Jan. 31 — she has uneven boobs! After the Pucci-clad Silver Linings Playbook actress told Jimmy Kimmel she was “sick and a little drunk” on the show, she opened up about her recent trip to the doctor. “Your producer made me do two shots of tequila and a beer. But the beer was my decision,” she admitted, before launching into a very personal story.

item.title: Why Paul McCartney Almost Quit Music After The Beatles Split
item.description: Paul McCartney is one of the greatest songwriters of all time. With over 150 songs that have made it onto the Billboard charts and 32 number-one hits, it is hard to imagine music without McCartney's influence both as a member of The Beatles, complete with straight-laced and controversial songs, and as a solo artist. His staggering net worth as the wealthiest of The Beatles proves that. RELATED: The Story Of How Barbara Walters Introduced Paul McCartney To His Wife Nancy Shevell McCartney is a true icon with generations of artists that look up to him.

At the time of the attack on December 15, 1991, Keith Yunk and his wife Anita were living in Largo, Florida, as a mixed family with both of their kids from prior marriages.  At around three in the morning, a murderer wearing a ski mask entered their bedroom and attacked the couple while they were sleeping. Anita Yunk was the victim of the man’s initial assault when he slashed her throat and hit her in the head with an axe.

item.title: Maximum Male Models Comment On Comparisons To Pretty Deadly
item.description: The Maximum Male Models (Mace and Mansoor) are known for being extremely outlandish and unafraid to be flamboyant. The duo has been compared to Pretty Deadly (Elton Prince and Kit Wilson) in that regard, and they’re aware of the similarities. Speaking to Alistair McGeorge of Metro, the Maximum Male Models commented on being compared to Pretty Deadly. “It’s funny, because you see how people think similarly, have the same ideas,” Mace said.

item.title: Punch stats show Francis Ngannou landed more power punches than Tyson Fury in controversial defeat
item.description: Tyson Fury vs Francis Ngannou turned out to be a lot closer than anyone had expected. Former UFC heavyweight champion Ngannou knocked Fury down in the third round, but 'The Gypsy King' went on to win by split decision. Although many people believed Ngannou deserved to win and he out-landed Fury through the fight in terms of power punches. When it comes to jabs, however, Fury landed 71 compared to Ngannou's 59.

item.title: Where is Walking Dead Shot? A Guide to the Filming Locations of the Zombie Apocalypse
item.description: The Walking Dead is one of the most popular and acclaimed television shows of all time, based on the comic book series by Robert Kirkman and Tony Moore. The show follows a group of survivors as they navigate a post-apocalyptic world overrun by zombies, or “walkers”, as they call them. The show has been praised for its realistic and gritty portrayal of the horror and drama of living in such a scenario, as well as its exploration of the human psyche and morality.
